In this speech delivered on the one-year anniversary of the attack on the U.S. Capitol, President Joe Biden reflects on the events of January 6, 2021, when a violent mob breached the Capitol in an attempt to overturn the election results. He emphasizes the importance of preserving democracy and preventing such an attack from happening again. The President condemns the former president for spreading lies about the election and refusing to accept the results. He also criticizes Republicans who are attempting to suppress the vote and undermine the democratic process. President Biden highlights the significance of the 2020 election, stating that it was the greatest demonstration of democracy in American history. He stresses the need to recognize the truth and reject the lies that are being spread. The President warns of the ongoing struggle between democracy and autocracy, both domestically and internationally, and urges Americans to stand up for the rule of law and the promise of America.